liament-future-world-cups-free-to-air-tv |title=Parliament to discuss keeping future World Cups on free-to-air TV |date=10 July 2018 }}</ref> According to Ofcom regulations, qualifying free-to-air channels are [[BBC One]], [[BBC Two]], [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]], [[Channel 4]] and [[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]].\n\n==Association football==\n===Television===\n{{see also|English football on television}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\" width=1000px\n|+Broadcasting contracts for football (television) \u2013 International matches\n!width=35%|Event\n!width=15%|Broadcasters (free-to-air)\n!width=15%|Broadcasters (paid)\n!width=15%|[[Ofcom]]\n!width=50%|Broadcast details\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | FIFA World Cup\n| BBC\n| rowspan=\"2\" | None\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{yes2}} [[Ofcom Code on Sports and Other Listed and Designated Events#Category A|Category A]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | All matches live on BBC & ITV with final live on both broadcasters in [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]]<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27750996 |title=BBC and ITV win rights to 2018 and 2022 Fifa World Cup finals |publisher=BBC Sport |date=7 June 2014 |accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| ITV\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |FIFA World Cup qualification\n| ITV\n| rowspan=\"3\" |\n| rowspan=\"3\" |\n| rowspan=\"3\" |\n*[[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|UEFA]] :<br>All matches (exclude England) live in English on Sky Sports.<br>England live matches and highlights of other matches in English on ITV.<br>Wales live matches in Welsh on S4C.<br>Highlights of NI, Scotland, and Wales matches in English on BBC, until 2022..\n*[[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|AFC]]:<br>Selected first and second round matches live on Mycujoo until 2020. \n*[[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|CONMEBOL]]:<br>TBA until 2021 or 2022.\n*[[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|CAF]]:<br>Selected matches live on FIFATV YouTube channel\n|-\n|BBC\n|-\n|YouTube\n|-\n| FIFA Women's Wor