present in the region. Hence, some differences can be expected relative to the resident population.)</small>''\n\n== Administration ==\nAdministratively, the municipality is divided into 4 civil parishes (''[[freguesia (Portugal)|freguesias]]''):<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 125|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=4 August 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref>\n* [[Alfena]]\n* Campo e Sobrado\n* [[Ermesinde]]\n* Valongo\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Valongo}}\n{{Municipalities of Porto}}\n{{PortoMA}}\n{{porto-geo-stub}}\n[[Category:Cities in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Porto District]]\n", "name_user": "WereSpielChequers", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo fixing, replaced: to to  \u2192  to,typo(s) fixed: ,  \u2192 ,  (2), occured \u2192 occurred", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valongo"}
{"title_page": "Jack Schofield (journalist)", "text_new": "{{short description|British technology journalist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name = Jack Schofield\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image = Jack Schofield in 2009.png\n| caption = Schofield in 2009\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = 1947\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{death date|2020|03|31 |df=y}}\n| death_place = \n| death_cause = [[Heart attack]]\n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates = \n| monuments = \n| residence = \n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| occupation = [[Journalist]]\n| years_active = \n| employer = \n| organization = \n| agent = \n| known_for = \n| notable_works = \n| style = \n| home_town = \n| television = \n| religion = \n| spouse = \n| partner = \n| children = \n| parents = \n| relatives = \n| awards = \n| website = \n| module = {{Listen| embed=yes |filename = Voice of Jack Schofield.ogg |title = Schofield's voice |type = speech |description = recorded in November 2012 }} \n}}\n'''Jack Schofield''' (1947<ref name=\"VIAF\">{{cite web |title=Schofield, Jack, 1947- |url=https://viaf.org/viaf/39387822/ |website=VIAF |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref> \u2013 31 March 2020)<ref name=guardian-20200401/> was a British technology journalist.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-06-27|title=Jack Schofield - Computer Editor @ The Guardian|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/person/jack-schofield#section-overview|website=[[Crunchbase]]}}</ref> He wrote the Ask Jack column for ''[[The Guardian]]''<ref name=\"thenquirer\">{{cite news|accessdate=2018-06-27|title=Guardian hack fails to Ask Jack about IE popups|url=https://www.theinquirer.net/inquirer/news/1004646/guardian-hack-fails-to-ask-jack-about-ie-popups|newspaper=[[The Inquirer]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191224060929/https://www.theinquirer.net/inquirer/news/1004646/guardian-hack-fails-to-ask-jack-about-ie-popups |archive-date=24 December 2019 |url-status=dead}}</ref> and preceding that covered technology for the newspaper from 1983 to 2010. He edited photography and computing periodicals and produced a number of books on photography and on computing, including ''The Darkroom Book'' (1981).\n\nHe died on 31 March 2020 following a [[heart attack]] on 27 March.<ref name=guardian-20200401>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/askjack/2020/apr/01/jack-schofield-guardian-ask-jack-tech-columnist-dies-at-72 |title=Jack Schofield, Guardian's Ask Jack tech columnist, dies at 72 |last=Hern |first=Alex |newspaper=The Guardian |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nSchofield edited various photography magazines during the 1970s:<ref name=\"theguardian-2009\">{{cite web|first1=Jack|last1=Schofield|first2=Charles|last2=Arthur|accessdate=27 June 2018|title=Guardian technology section 1983-2009, by the people who edited it|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2009/dec/16/guardian-technology-section|date=16 December 2009|website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> ''Photo Technique,'' ''Film Making,'' ''You & Your Camera'' (a [[partwork]]), and ''Zoom'' as well as the journal of the [[Royal Photographic Society]], ''The Photographic Journal.''<ref name=\"theguardian-2007\">{{cite web|first1=Jack|last1=Schofield|accessdate=2018-06-27|title=Ars Technica reviews Adobe's Lightroom|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/blog/2007/feb/21/arstechnicare1|date=21 February 2007|website=The Guardian}}</ref>\n\nIn 1983, he started writing a weekly computer column in Futures Micro Guardian, from its first issue, in ''[[The Guardian]].''<ref name=\"theguardian-2009\"/> He also became editor of the monthly ''[[Practical Computing]]''<ref name=\"theguardian-2009\"/> in 1984. In September 1985 he joined ''The Guardian''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s staff to launch Computer Guardian, the newspaper's weekly computer supplement.<ref name=\"theguardian-2009\"/> He continued to cover technology for ''The Guardian'' until 2010 when he switched to solely writing the newspaper's ''Ask Jack'' column.<ref name=\"thenquirer\"/><ref>{{cite web|first1=Jack|last1=Schofield|accessdate=27 June 2018|title=What happened to Ask Jack?|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/askjack/2010/jan/18/ask-jack-is-back|date=18 January 2010|website=The Guardian}}</ref>\n\nSchofield also wrote on computing for [[Reuters]]<ref>{{cite web|first1=Reuters|last1=Editorial|accessdate=27 June 2018|title=Columns|url=https://www.reuters.com/journalists/jack-schofield|website=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> and blogged for [[ZDNet]].<ref name=zdnet>{{cite web |url=https://www.zdnet.com/meet-the-team/uk/jack-schofield/47/ |title=Jack Schofield - Freelance blogger |last=Schofield |first=Jack |publisher=ZDNet |access-date=1 April 2020}}</ref><ref>Jack Schofield, \"[http://www.storyoftheweb.org.uk/report/storyoftheweb.pdf Nominet Presents The Story of the Web: Celebrating 25 years of the World Wide Web]\". [[Nominet UK]]. Accessed 27 June 2018</ref> He produced a number of books on photography and on computing.<ref name=\"theguardian-2007\"/>\n\n==Publications==\n*''The Darkroom Book: the comprehensive step-by-step guide to processing your colour or black-and-white photographs.'' Schofield was consulting editor.\n**London: Spring, 1981, 1982. Feltham, UK: [[Elsevier|Newnes]], 1983. {{ISBN|9780600353997}}.\n**New York: [[Ziff Davis]], 1981. {{ISBN|9780871651068}}.\n**New York: [[Watson-Guptill|Amphoto]], 1981, 1985, 1987, 1988. {{ISBN|9780817437572}}.\n*''Photographing People.'' [[Hachette (publisher)|Littlehampton Book Services]], 1982. {{ISBN|978-0600384731}}.\n*''Nude and Glamour Photography.'' You & Your Camera Photography Series. Glasgow: [[William Collins, Sons|Collins]], 1981, 1982. Schofield was consultant editor. {{ISBN|978-0004116396}}.\n*''How Famous Photographers Work.'' New York: Amphoto, 1983. Edited by Schofield. {{ISBN|9780817440022}}.\n*''Improve Your Camera Techniques.'' Feltham, UK: Newnes, 1985. Edited by Schofield. {{ISBN|9780600332657}}.\n*''The Guardian Guide to Microcomputing.'' Oxford, UK; New York: [[Wiley-Blackwell|Blackwell]], 1985. Hardback, {{ISBN|978-0631143031}}. Paperback, {{ISBN|9780631143048}}. \"A selection of the author's columns from the MicroFutures page of the Guardian, rewritten and revised\".<ref>{{cite book|first1=Jack|last1=Schofield|title=The Guardian guide to microcomputing|publisher=Blackwell|location=Oxford, UK; New York, NY, USA|isbn=9780631143048|oclc=11786409}}</ref>\n*''The Hutchinson Dictionary of Computing, Mulitmedia, and the Internet.'' By Schofield, [[Wendy M. Grossman]] and David Goul. Oxford, UK: Helicon, 1996, 1997. {{ISBN|978-1859861592}}.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Twitter|jackschofield}}\n*[https://www.theguardian.com/profile/jackschofield Schofield's profile page at ''The Guardian'']\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Schofield, Jack}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:British magazine editors]]\n[[Category:The Guardian journalists]]\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British technology journalist}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name = Jack Schofield\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image = Jack Schofield in 2009.png\n| caption = Schofield in 2009\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = 1947\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{death date|2020|03|31 |df=y}}\n| death_place = \n| death_cause = [[Heart attack]]\n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates = \n| monuments = \n| residence = \n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| occupation = [[Journalist]]\n| years_active = \n| employer = \n| organization = \n| agent = \n| known_for = \n| notable_works = \n| style = \n| home_town = \n| television = \n| religion = \n| spouse = \n| partner = \n| children = \n| parents = \n| relatives = \n| awards = \n| website = \n| module = {{Listen| embed=yes |filename = Voice of Jack Schofield.ogg |titl